TITLE: Homebuyers rush to riskier loans, as tariff turmoil pushes interest rates higher
SUMMARY: Mortgage rates moved sharply higher last week, causing a drop in mortgage demand and a surge in homebuyers seeking riskier loans.

TITLE: Mortgage rates surge over 7% as tariffs hit bond market
SUMMARY: Mortgage rates surged over 7% to end the week, after massive volatility in bond markets surrounding President Donald Trump's tariff agenda.

TITLE: Here's how China could crush the U.S. housing market
SUMMARY: China is one of largest owners of U.S. mortgages. There is growing concern that in retaliation for tariffs the country could sell them, causing rates to rise.

TITLE: Weekly mortgage demand jumped 20% last week, as tariff volatility briefly tanked rates
SUMMARY: Mortgage demand surged to the highest level since September as Trump's tariff plans caused interest rates to drop. But those rates are now back up.

TITLE: Mortgage rates slingshot higher as tariff uncertainty roils markets
SUMMARY: After falling sharply last week, mortgage rates rose again this week, wiping out any advantage to the spring housing market. Tariffs were behind the volatility.

TITLE: Mortgage rates sink on tariffs, but housing costs are still near a record high
SUMMARY: Mortgage rates fell sharply Thursday, following the Trump administration's tariff announcement, but a huge share of Americans still can't afford to buy a home.

TITLE: Manhattan's luxury real estate market sees best first quarter in six years
SUMMARY: Manhattan apartment sales rose 29% in the first quarter, and the total value of apartment sales in the city reached $5.7 billion, up 56%.

TITLE: Mortgage rates and demand seem stuck in a holding pattern, as markets await tariff news
SUMMARY: Mortgage rates and demand have moved in a narrow range recently, as uncertainty over tariffs weighs on the markets.

TITLE: Homeownership is 'an investment,' Maryland governor says. High prices mean fewer young adults can benefit
SUMMARY: Since 1980, median home prices have increased much faster than median household incomes, research finds. For some, that is putting homeownership out of reach.

TITLE: We're buying more shares of 2 stocks as the broader market sinks further
SUMMARY: We're making a couple of small buys to take advantage of Friday's lower prices.

TITLE: KB Home unveils its first 'fire-resilient' community in Southern California
SUMMARY: KB Home is the first large production builder to unveil a community designed to fire-resilient standards by the Insurance Institute for Business & Home Safety.

TITLE: Mortgage demand from homebuyers is strongest in nearly two months, but that's not saying a lot
SUMMARY: Mortgage rates didn't move much last week, but demand from homebuyers for loans rose to the highest level in nearly two months. Rising inventory may be why.

TITLE: Federal housing agency will not cut Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac loan limits, new director says
SUMMARY: The new director of the FHFA said he has no intention of shrinking the limit on loans bought and guaranteed by Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac.

TITLE: These 10 Asian markets offer high returns on short-term rentals — half top $40,000 a year
SUMMARY: Vacation rentals in Hakuba, Japan can bring in, on average, more than $60,000 a year in revenue for short-term rental investors, according to data company AirDNA.

TITLE: Cramer is not bothered by near-term headwinds facing one of his favorite stocks
SUMMARY: Jim Cramer believes Home Depot could be a major winner this year.

TITLE: Tariff fears are raising construction costs by up to 20%, says Related Group CEO
SUMMARY: Related said the high end of the real estate market remains strong, especially in Florida.

TITLE: China's property market edges toward an inflection point
SUMMARY: UBS analysts on Wednesday became the latest to raise expectations that China's struggling real estate market is close to stabilizing.

TITLE: February home resales jump much more than expected, despite higher mortgage rates
SUMMARY: The median price of a home sold in February was $398,400, up 3.8% from the same time last year.

TITLE: World's largest sovereign wealth fund invests $740 million in London's Covent Garden
SUMMARY: Norway's $1.8 trillion sovereign wealth fund on Thursday said that it struck a deal to buy a quarter of London's iconic Covent Garden.

TITLE: Federal Reserve holds interest rates steady: What that means for mortgages, credit cards and more
SUMMARY: The Fed is staying on the sidelines, for now, but some consumer loan rates are changing.

TITLE: Here’s when to list your home for sale this spring — it could sell for up to $27,000 more, data shows
SUMMARY: The spring housing market is a period of high homebuying and selling activity. Listing your home in early April could bring in extra cash, report finds.

TITLE: Weekly mortgage demand pulls back, as interest rates rise for the first time in 9 weeks
SUMMARY: Mortgage rates fell for the first time in nine weeks, causing a pullback in mortgage demand, especially refinancing.

TITLE: Federal Reserve is likely to hold interest rates steady next week. But some consumer loans are getting cheaper
SUMMARY: High interest rates have put pressure on households, but some borrowing costs are starting to ease, even with the Fed on the sidelines.

TITLE: DC housing market shows signs of cracks amid mass federal layoffs
SUMMARY: The number of active listings in the D.C. metro area is sharply higher compared with last year.

TITLE: Tariffs to add as much as $10,000 to the cost of the average new home, trade association says
SUMMARY: "The tariffs act as a tax on American builders, home buyers and consumers," the National Association of Home Builders said.

TITLE: This step is ‘really important’ if you plan to sell your home in 2025, economist says
SUMMARY: Selling your house takes more than just putting up a “for sale” sign. Getting the right asking  price is a really important step, experts say.

TITLE: Take a look inside the world's largest 3D printed housing development
SUMMARY: The world's largest 3D printed community is now open and mostly sold. Take a look inside the homes and hear from residents about what it's like to live there.

TITLE: Weekly mortgage demand surges 11% higher, as interest rates dropped for the sixth straight week
SUMMARY: Mortgage demand for both homebuying and refinancing reacted to yet another drop in mortgage rates, which are now down for the sixth straight week.

TITLE: These are the most competitive rental markets in the U.S.
SUMMARY: Even with a record amount of new supply, demand for rental apartments is soaring. That has the competition heating up.

TITLE: The Federal Housing Administration could face layoffs — what that may mean for homebuyers
SUMMARY: The Federal Housing Administration, a major provider of low-down-payment loan options for first-time homebuyers, is facing a staff cut. What you should know.
